<TITLE> ctivist slams HSBC bonuses before strategy update </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 LONDON, Nov 23 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - US activist investor Knight Vinke stepped up a campaign against HSBC Holdings, saying the bank's bonus plan for senior executives was "legally void", ahead of a strategy update by the bank on Friday. Knight Vinke said HSBC's 2005 share plan for executives "was both misleading and insufficient" and as a result the shareholder resolution approving the plan is legally void. It said summaries of the bonus scheme sent to shareholders "gave the impression that the performance targets were significantly more demanding than they are in reality". The investor, which holds about 0.3 percent of HSBC shares, took out national newspaper advertisements highlighting the issue. HSBC is due to make a strategy presentation to analysts on Friday afternoon. Knight Vinke has previously urged HSBC to consider "radical solutions" such as liquidating the majority of its investment bank arm to help reverse what it describes as "perennial stock market underperformance compared to peers". On Nov. 5, HSBC became the West's biggest bank by market capitalisation after its shares outperformed leading rivals in the fallout from the US housing cris
